    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl><ptr target="#oliverio1929"/>, p. 143, n. <citedRange>18</citedRange>, fig. 41</bibl>, whence 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>9.312</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>030100</citedRange></bibl>. 
                    Cf. <bibl><ptr target="#lazzarini1976"/>, p. 274, n. <citedRange>697.c</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#maffre2007"/>, p. 168, n. <citedRange>3</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><supplied reason="lost">Τõ</supplied> <persName type="divine" ref="#Apollo"><name nymRef="#Ἀπόλλων"><supplied reason="lost">Ἀπόλο̄</supplied>νος</name></persName> <w>δεκ<supplied reason="lost">άτα</supplied></w>.
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p><app loc="1"><lem resp="#SEG">δεκ<supplied reason="lost">άτα</supplied></lem>
                <rdg resp="#oliverio1929">δεκ<supplied reason="lost">άταν</supplied></rdg>
                    <rdg resp="#maffre2007">δεκ<supplied reason="lost">άτα</supplied></rdg>
                    <rdg resp="#maffre2007">δεκ<supplied reason="lost">άταν</supplied></rdg>
                </app>    
                </p>
 </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
            <p>Dîme d'Apollon.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
            <p>Apollo's tithe.</p></div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
            <p>Decima di Apollo.</p>
            </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>As the editor of SEG rightly put it, it is impossible to have the accusative of the word 'tithe' with the genitive of the god's name.</p>
                <p>Lazzarini took the readings of SEG without mentioning any restoration.</p>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
